Phase 21: Text Variables v3.0 (v3.0)                       COMPLETE

Variable Scoping — SERVER-SIDE

Scope Levels:
  LOCAL (0)    — cleared on scene end (ClearScreen)
                 Used for: temp values within a single screen
  SESSION (1)  — persists for connection duration
                 Used for: user prefs, navigation, form data
  PERSIST (2)  — saved to disk, survives between sessions
                 Used for: saved settings, statistics

Scope Lifecycle:
  Connection starts
    Load persistent vars from disk
      Scene loads
        Local vars created
        Scene ends (ClearScreen) -> local vars cleared
      Next scene loads
        Session vars still available
      User disconnects
        Save persistent vars to disk
        Session vars cleared

✓  $RESET(PAL)$ — palette reset during text expansion
✓  $RESET(ALL)$ — full engine state reset during text expansion
✓  Extended variables: $PIXFMT$, $CANVASW$, $CANVASH$, $RFFFONT$, $MAFRES$
✓  Variable scoping: LOCAL (scene), SESSION (connection), PERSIST (disk)

v3.0 Phase 21 API — SERVER-SIDE (Variable Scoping):
Procedure DefineVarScoped (Name, Value: String; Scope: Byte; Required: Boolean)
  Scope: RIP_SCOPE_LOCAL (0), RIP_SCOPE_SESSION (1), RIP_SCOPE_PERSIST (2)
Procedure KillLocalVars — clear LOCAL scope (auto-called by ClearScreen)
Procedure KillSessionVars — clear SESSION scope (call on disconnect)

v3.0 Phase 21 Extended Variables:
$RESET(PAL)$ — resets palette to EGA defaults, inserts nothing
$RESET(ALL)$ — full Reset, inserts nothing
$PIXFMT$     — current pixel format (INDEXED8, RGB24, RGB32)
$CANVASW$    — canvas width in pixels
$CANVASH$    — canvas height in pixels
$RFFFONT$    — active RFF scalable font name (empty if none)
$MAFRES$     — active MAF bitmap font resolution (empty if none)

See CLIENTSERVER.md for full architecture and data flow diagrams.

Phase 22: Advanced Multimedia (v3.0)                       COMPLETE

SERVER-SIDE Audio Architecture:
  AudioLoad(stream, file) ──► AudioPlay(stream)
       │                          │
       ▼                          ▼
  [store reference]         [state = PLAYING]
                                  │
                            AudioPause / AudioStop
                                  │
  WAV Streaming:                  ▼
    WAVStreamStart ──► WAVStreamFeed ──► WAVStreamEnd
       [format]         [chunks]          [flush]
                            │
                      ringbuf.pas -> wavplay.pas

  MIDI:  MIDILoad(file) -> host parses via mididec.pas
  Cues:  CueAdd(frame, action) -> CueProcess fires at frame
  BgAudio: SetBgAudio -> BgAudioTransition (crossfade)

✓  MIDI playback — MIDILoad/MIDIFree
✓  Audio mixing — 4-stream AudioLoad/Play/Pause/Stop/SetVolume
✓  Video frame sequences — FrameCounter + CueProcess
✓  Timed event scripting — CueAdd/CueClear/CueProcess (64 cue points)
✓  Background audio — SetBgAudio/BgAudioTransition
✓  WAV streaming — WAVStreamStart/Feed/End

